The paper discusses defense methods against adversarial attacks in the cyber security domain, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which are often associated with neural networks and fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of defense methods, which could also fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
